# IRIM R Workshops: Introduction to R
# Authors and Contributors

## Lesson Adaptation

Kathryn Napier
  Independent Research Institute of Mongolia (IRIM)
  https://github.com/kathrynnapier

Kathryn Napier adapted and developed this workshop series for IRIM, combining
and modifying material from the two Carpentries source lessons listed below.


## Source Lesson 1: Data Analysis and Visualization in R for Ecologists

Original lesson: https://datacarpentry.github.io/R-ecology-lesson/
Repository:      https://github.com/datacarpentry/R-ecology-lesson

Authors - see Zenodo record https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1250065

## Source Lesson 2: R for Social Scientists

Original lesson: https://datacarpentry.github.io/r-socialsci/
Repository:      https://github.com/datacarpentry/r-socialsci

Authors - see Zenodo record https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.597005

## The Carpentries

Both source lessons are part of the Data Carpentry curriculum, maintained by
The Carpentries (https://carpentries.org). Carpentries lessons are licensed
under the Creative Commons Attribution (CC BY 4.0) licence.
